definition.value: A protein complex that contains the zinc finger transcription factor GATA2, the LIM domain protein Lmo2 (RBTN2), the basic helix-loop-helix protein TAL1 and its binding partner TCF3. The complex is involved transcriptional regulation in hematopoiesis.
A SNARE complex that contains synaptotagmin, synaptobrevin 2 (VAMP2), SNAP-25, syntaxin 1a, syntaxin1b, Rab3a, and complexin II (or orthologs thereof).
A SNARE complex that contains synaptotagmin, synaptobrevin 2 (VAMP2), SNAP-25, syntaxin 1a, syntaxin1b, and Rab3a (or orthologs thereof).
A protein complex that consists of an alphav-beta3 integrin complex bound to CD47 (also known as IAP).

label.value: mitochondrial light strand promoter anti-sense binding

definition.value: Interacting selectively and non-covalently with the anti-sense strand of the light strand promoter, a promoter located on the light, or cytosine-rich, strand of mitochondrial DNA.

label.value: mitochondrial heavy strand promoter anti-sense binding

definition.value: Interacting selectively and non-covalently with the anti-sense strand of the heavy strand promoter, a promoter located on the heavy, or guanine-rich, strand of mitochondrial DNA.

label.value: mitochondrial light strand promoter sense binding

definition.value: Interacting selectively and non-covalently with the sense strand of the light strand promoter, a promoter located on the light, or cytosine-rich, strand of mitochondrial DNA.

label.value: mitochondrial heavy strand promoter sense binding

definition.value: Interacting selectively and non-covalently with the sense strand of the heavy strand promoter, a promoter located on the heavy, or guanine-rich, strand of mitochondrial DNA.
A protein complex that contains beta-catenin and TCF7L2 (TCF4), binds to the TCF DNA motif within a promoter element, and is involved in the regulation of WNT target gene transcription.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with high mobility group box 1 (HMBGB1).

label.value: high mobility group box 1 receptor activity

definition.value: Combining with high mobility group box 1 (HMBGB1) and transmitting the signal from one side of the membrane to the other to initiate a change in cell activity.

label.value: endosome to plasma membrane transport vesicle

definition.value: A transport vesicle that mediates transport from the endosome to the plasma membrane, and fuses with the plasma membrane to release various cargo molecules, such as proteins or hormones, by exocytosis.

A transport vesicle that mediates transport from an intracellular compartment to the plasma membrane, and fuses with the plasma membrane to release various cargo molecules, such as proteins or hormones, by exocytosis.
A protein complex that contains beta-glucuronidase and the carboxyl esterase egasyn -  formation of the complex causes beta-glucuronidase to be retained in the endoplasmic reticulum.
A procollagen-proline 4-dioxygenase complex that contains alpha subunits of the type I isoform -  its activity is readily inhibited by poly(L-proline).
A procollagen-proline 4-dioxygenase complex that contains alpha subunits of the type II isoform -  its activity is inhibited by poly(L-proline) only at high concentrations.
A procollagen-proline 4-dioxygenase complex that contains alpha subunits of the type III isoform.

A protein complex that couples SAGA-dependent gene expression to mRNA export at the inner side of the nuclear pore complex (NPC). The TREX-2 complex is tethered to the inner side of the NPC via the nucleoporins Nup1 and Nup60 -  in S. cerevisiae it contains Sac3p, Thp1p, Sus1p and Cdc31p.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with the oxidized form, NADP+, of nicotinamide-adenine dinucleotide phosphate, a coenzyme involved in many redox and biosynthetic reactions.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with the reduced form, NADPH, of nicotinamide-adenine dinucleotide phosphate, a coenzyme involved in many redox and biosynthetic reactions.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with the oxidized form, NAD, of nicotinamide adenine dinucleotide, a coenzyme involved in many redox and biosynthetic reactions.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with the reduced form, NADH, of nicotinamide adenine dinucleotide, a coenzyme involved in many redox and biosynthetic reactions.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with ammonium ions (NH4+).
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with glutamine, 2,5-diamino-5-oxopentanoic acid.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a common mediator SMAD signaling protein.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with an inhibitory SMAD signaling protein.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a receptor-regulated SMAD signaling protein.

A protein complex that is involved in the repair of DNA double-strand breaks and, in mammals, V(D)J recombination events. It consists of the DNA-dependent protein kinase catalytic subunit (DNA-PKcs) and the DNA end-binding heterodimer Ku.

A protein complex that plays a role in DNA double-strand break repair via nonhomologous end joining. Such complexes typically contain a specialized DNA ligase (e.g. Lig4 in eukaryotes) and one or more proteins that bind to DNA ends.
A nonhomologous end joining complex that contains one or more Ku monomers and one or more DNA ligase molecules from the LigC or LigD family, and mediates nonhomologous end joining in bacteria.
A protein complex that contains DNA ligase III and XRCC1, and is involved in base excision repair.
A protein complex formed by the association of the serine-threonine protein kinase Raf-1 with the beta and gamma subunits of a heterotrimeric G protein.
A protein complex that contains the epidermal growth factor receptor (EGFR) and the adaptor protein Shc, and is involved in linking EGFR activation to the p21-Ras pathway.
A protein complex that contains the epidermal growth factor receptor (EGFR) and Grb2, and is involved in linking EGFR activation to the p21-Ras pathway.
A protein complex that contains Grb2 and the adaptor protein Shc, and is involved in linking epidermal growth factor receptor (EGFR) activation to the p21-Ras pathway.
A transcriptional repressor complex that contains a heterodimer of the bHLH-ZIP proteins Mad and Max, plus mSin3A, a homolog of the yeast Sin3p.
A transcriptional repressor complex that contains a heterodimer of the bHLH-ZIP proteins Mad and Max, plus mSin3B, a homolog of the yeast Sin3p.

A protein complex formed by the association of the Bruton tyrosine protein kinase Btk, which is implicated in mammalian X-linked immunodeficiencies, with the beta and gamma subunits of a heterotrimeric G protein.
An integrin complex that comprises one alphaIIb subunit and one beta3 subunit.
A transcriptional repressor complex that consists of a heterodimer of the bHLH-ZIP proteins Mad and Max.
Catalysis of the reaction -  S-adenosyl-L-methionine + laricitrin -eq- S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + syringetin.

A transcription elongation factor complex that suppresses RNA polymerase II pausing, and may act by promoting proper alignment of the 3'-end of nascent transcripts with the polymerase catalytic site. Consists of a transcriptionally active Elongin A subunit (abut 100 kDa)and two smaller Elongin B (about 18 kDa) and Elongin C (about 15 kDa)subunits.
A protein complex that is formed by the association of a heterodimeric interleukin-4 receptor complex with an interleukin-4 molecule.
A long, thin cell projection that contains F-actin and tubulin, with microtubules centrally located and F-actin peripherally located.
Catalysis of the reaction -  galactose-1-phosphate + H2O -eq- galactose + phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  D-galactose-1-phosphate + H2O -eq- D-galactose + phosphate.

A histone acetyltransferase complex that acetylates nucleosomal H3 and H2B and is required for the expression of a subset of Pol II-transcribed genes. The budding yeast complex includes the acetyltransferase Gcn5p, several proteins of the Spt and Ada families, and several TBP-associate proteins (TAFs) -  analogous complexes in other species have analogous compositions, and usually contain homologs of the yeast proteins.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + H2O -eq- ADP + phosphate. This reaction requires the presence of a tubulin dimer to accelerate release of ADP and phosphate.
A protein complex that consists of an alphav-beta3 integrin complex bound to the alpha3 chain of type VI collagen -  the integrin binds most strongly to unfolded collagen.
A protein complex that consists of an alpha1-beta1 integrin complex bound to a type VI collagen triple helix containing an alpha3(VI) chain.
